    {
      "letter": "c",
      "prompt": "The funnel contains liquid that is draining from the bottom. At the instant when the height of the liquid is $h = 3$ inches, the radius of the surface of the liquid is decreasing at a rate of $\\frac{1}{5}$ inch per second. At this instant, what is the rate of change of the height of the liquid with respect to time?",
      "point_value": 3,
